<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}-{6}{y}={20}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{x}+{7}{y}={49}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({7},{6}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}+-{6}{y}={20}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}={20}-{\left(-{6}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{20}-{\left(-{6}{y}\right)}}}{{8}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1}{\left(\frac{{{20}-{\left(-{6}{y}\right)}}}{{8}}\right)}+{7}{y}={49}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{1}}{{8}}\cdot{\left({20}\right)}-\frac{{1}}{{8}}{\left(-{6}\right)}{y}+{7}{y}={49}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2.5}-{\left({0.75}\right)}{y}+{7}{y}={49}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{0.75}{y}+{\left({7}\right)}{y}={49}-{2.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{0.75}{y}+{\left({7}\right)}{y}={46.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left({0.75}+{\left({7}\right)}\right)}{y}={46.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7.75}{y}={46.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{46.5}}{{7.75}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={6}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}+-{6}{\left({6}\right)}={20}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}+{\left(-{36}\right)}={20}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}={20}-{\left(-{36}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}={56}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{56}}{{8}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={7}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({7},{6}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

